1 Bonedancer<br>
1 Skald (me=)<br>
2 Berzerkers<br>
1 savage<br>
1 runemaster<br>
1 shaman<br>
1 random guy.<br>
We were hunting in the battlegrounds the other day with this group, holding the ck, and quite frankly I did not do good in RVR in the battlegrounds.  I had about maybe 10-20 kills the entire night.  First my hammer wasnt swinging as fast or as hard, is this because im fighting other people?<br>
Secondly, my DD songs cancel out the speed song, it has always happened before, but is there anyway to not have it cancel out the speed song?  <br>
My only kills were on running casters or sitting casters with DD shouts, and I could not really kill any other class without support, is this normal?<br>
Also, it seemed like my snare and mez didnt last long whatsoever, do I need to stand still to cast these? <br>
Sorry if Im being kinda generalized, but reading all of the good stuff about skalds I was kinda wondering if the Skald class wasnt for me.  <br>
Also for the people who dont flame me =) could you please post any RVR strategies that you have for oncoming attacks, defending keeps and openfield battle against other classes and tanks.  Like when to mez, who to snare and who to go after first? <br>
Thanks, and sorry for this post being so unorganized, just so many questions =)<br>
<br>
19 Skald Perceival,<br>
Chewen<br>
<br>
PS-Respecing to axe once I hit 20, Many of the people ive talked to are saying to switch =) Thanks again.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luckymike83>LuckyMike83</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/11/03 11:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=576.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Also</span><hr size=1> Also, my end Spec chart template thing is looking like this, <br>
