<br>
Your DD's will always break speed.. since its a combat action.<br>
Your mez and snare probably arent lasting long because any attack will break them.<br>
Whats you're spec in weapon like? That has a big effect on damage.<br>
<br>
Overall, a skald is a support class.. its good to remember that. In RvR your real skill is mobility, which means a LOT in combat. Dont expect to be a zerker with speed, cause you'll never do that kind of damage <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Just figure out what your strengths are and perfect them.<br>
<br>
Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/12/03 4:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=576.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well</span><hr size=1> Any kind of &quot;offensive&quot;  action will break speed. It's NOT like the bard song in EQ.<br>
<br>
There is no difference in swing times between PvE and RvR. Some enemy players can cast attack speed debuff spells on you, but that's it.<br>
<br>
You'll do generally less damage on players than on monsters, because players can use items to increase their resistance to &quot;melee&quot; (crush, slash and thrust resist). Also, your hammer has bonuses or penalties agaist some armor types (look at this thread  : <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showMessage?topicID=535.topic">pub36.ezboard.com/fteamsk...=535.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> )<br>
<br>
At lower levels, mez won't last long because it's duration is based on the level of the spell, and at battlegrounds level it is very short. At higher levels, your mez will work decently in PvE, but will be merely moe than an interrupt on a well equiped tank  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Your snare should last a reasonable amount of time, however, note that snare and root spells do not work like in EQ : they break immediately when en enemy is hit, perhaps this is what was happening ?<br>
<br>
Although it is not as bad in the battlegrounds than in the level 50+ RvR, skalds have a very, very difficult time killing most of the melee classes in the game. Play a savage, zerker, or shadowblade if you want to kill people.<br>
<br>
Skalds role is to bring a very beneficial ability (speed) to your groupe. This is a role that should not be downplayed, but skalds pay a lot in relative power (espacially against the other so called &quot;support hybrids&quot; and &quot;melee hybrids&quot;) for speed. It's up to you to decide, the skald is not a bad class, but nowhere near as powerful as it is commonly hyped to be.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luckymike83>LuckyMike83</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/12/03 6:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=576.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yeah</span><hr size=1> Yeah I was thinking skalds could go hand in hand with the other melee classes on the field.  As regards to the snare yes the person was getting hit, so I guess it would cancel it out , the mez would just break within like 3 seconds on its own,<br>
